FBIS4-47837 "drafr086_c_94028" FBIS-AFR-94-086 Daily Report 3 May 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA State of Emergency Lifted for W. Transvaal Towns State of Emergency Lifted for W. Transvaal Towns MB0305143594 Johannesburg SAPA in English 1311 GMT 3 May 94 MB0305143594 Johannesburg SAPA English BFN [Text] Potchefstroom May 3 SAPA -- The state of emergency imposed on 15 Western Transvaal towns last week was lifted on Tuesday [3 May] morning. Deputy regional commissioner of police Brig Izak Smalman said the state of emergency declared on April 28 in the magisterial districts of Potchefstroom, Swartruggens, Marico, Lichtenburg, Coligny, Ventersdorp, Delareyville, Schweizer-Reneke, Wolmeransstad, Bloemhof, Klerksdorp, Koster, Christiana, Oberholzer and Rustenburg had been lifted.
